Amiable Blunder		KEY:Trait ~ Amiable Blunder				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.BasicTrait.SocialTrait									PREMULT:1,[PREVAREQ:BypassTraitRestriction,1],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.SocialTrait],[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Trait ~ Amiable Blunder]												DESC:Once per day when you fail a Diplomacy check by 5 or more and would cause an NPC's attitude toward you to worsen, you can immediately attempt another Diplomacy check against the same DC as a free action. If you succeed at this second Diplomacy check, the character's attitude doesn't change, as though you had failed the original check by 4 or less.																																																																																																																																																												SOURCEPAGE:p.9
Balancer's Banishing	KEY:Trait ~ Balancer's Banishing			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.BasicTrait.MagicTrait									PREMULT:1,[PREVAREQ:BypassTraitRestriction,1],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.MagicTrait],[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Trait ~ Balancer's Banishing]											DESC:As long as you remain neutral, whenever you cast a spell that would send an outsider with the chaotic, evil, good, or lawful subtype back to its home plane, the spell's saving throw DC increases by 1.																																																																																																																																																																																					SOURCEPAGE:p.9
Inexorable Authority	KEY:Trait ~ Inexorable Authority			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.BasicTrait.SocialTrait									PREMULT:1,[PREVAREQ:BypassTraitRestriction,1],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.SocialTrait],[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Trait ~ Inexorable Authority]											DESC:You gain a +2 trait bonus on Intimidate checks when enforcing or pronouncing a lawful judgment that you're legitimately deputed to enforce or pronounce.																																																																																																																																																																																													SOURCEPAGE:p.7
No Escape			KEY:Trait ~ No Escape					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.BasicTrait.CombatTrait									PREMULT:1,[PREVAREQ:BypassTraitRestriction,1],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.CombatTrait],[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Trait ~ No Escape]													DESC:You gain a +1 trait bonus on combat maneuver checks to lawfully and nonlethally restrain a creature you've witnessed commit a crime.																																																																																																																																																																																																	SOURCEPAGE:p.7
Unabashed Gall		KEY:Trait ~ Unabashed Gall				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.BasicTrait.SocialTrait									PREMULT:1,[PREVAREQ:BypassTraitRestriction,1],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.SocialTrait],[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Trait ~ Unabashed Gall]												DESC:Whenever you commit an unexpected and outrageously unlawful act that would elicit a hostile response, you may attempt a Bluff check opposed by the opponent's Sense Motive check. If successful, you (and any knowing allies) may act in a surprise round. For each such ally, you take a cumulative -2 penalty on your Bluff check. If your Bluff check fails, there is no surprise round. Regardless of whether your Bluff check succeeds, you and any such allies treat your initiative checks as though you had each rolled a 1.																																																																																																																																	SOURCEPAGE:p.11
Unpredictable Reactions	KEY:Trait ~ Unpredictable Reactions			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.BasicTrait.CombatTrait									PREMULT:1,[PREVAREQ:BypassTraitRestriction,1],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.CombatTrait],[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Trait ~ Unpredictable Reactions]										DESC:You gain a +1 trait bonus on attack rolls made during the surprise round of combat.																																																																																																																																																																																																									SOURCEPAGE:p.11

Commercial Savvy		KEY:Trait ~ Commercial Savvy				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.RegionalTrait										PREMULT:1,[PREVAREQ:BypassTraitRestriction,1],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.RegionalTrait],[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Trait ~ Commercial Savvy]		PREREGION:Katapesh						DESC:Whenever you buy from or sell to a merchant, you treat a settlement's Base Value and Purchase Limit (GameMastery Guide p204) as 10%% higher.																																																																																																																																																																																															SOURCEPAGE:p.12
Elemental Endowment	KEY:Trait ~ Elemental Endowment			CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.RegionalTrait										PREMULT:1,[PREVAREQ:BypassTraitRestriction,1],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.RegionalTrait],[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Trait ~ Elemental Endowment]		PREREGION:Osirion							DESC:As an immediate action, once per day when you cast a spell with the air, earth, fire, or water descriptor, you can gain a number of temporary hit points equal to the spell's level. This effect lasts for 1 minute.																																																																																																																																																																																			SOURCEPAGE:p.13
Evident Supporter		KEY:Trait ~ Evident Supporter				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.RegionalTrait										PREMULT:1,[PREVAREQ:BypassTraitRestriction,1],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.RegionalTrait],[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Trait ~ Evident Supporter]		PREREGION:Galt							DESC:The Sense Motive DC needed for a governmental functionary (such as police) in a large town or larger settlement to gain a hunch about your trustworthiness is 25 (instead of 20). On a failed check, you're seen as trustworthy regardless of the situation.																																																																																																																																																																													SOURCEPAGE:p.12
Justiciar			KEY:Trait ~ Justiciar					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Trait.RegionalTrait										PREMULT:1,[PREVAREQ:BypassTraitRestriction,1],[!PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.RegionalTrait],[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Trait ~ Justiciar]			PREREGION:Rahadoum						DESC:You gain a +1 trait bonus on Diplomacy and Knowledge (local) checks to settle disputes or arbitrate laws. Once per day if you succeed at an Intimidate check to demoralize a foe who has repudiated or ignored a pronounced judgment you've made, you may choose to cause the creature to be sickened instead of shaken. The duration of the effect remains the same.																																																																																																																																																											SOURCEPAGE:p.12

